This paper deals with the problem of learning in Constrained Markov Decision Processes (CMDPs), which is a subfield of reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization and regret analysis, which are common topics in machine learning, leading to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also deals with decision-making and control, which are topics in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the dual formulation of CMDPs, which is a topic in mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
